## TypeScript Standards

- Enable strict mode (`"strict": true` in tsconfig.json)
- Prefer `interface` over `type` for object shapes that can be extended
- Avoid `any`; use `unknown` and narrow types with guards
- Use `const` by default; `let` only when reassignment is necessary
- Prefer named exports over default exports for better refactoring support
- Use `async/await` over `.then()` chains
- Co-locate types with the code that uses them; avoid a single global `types.ts`
- Use `satisfies` for type-safe object literals where inference is desired
